-- 1-bit cosine distance ranks by sign (used to be constant 1 for every row)
0	2	2
1	1.75	1.75
2	1.75	1.75
3	1.5	1.5
4	1.75	1.75
0	2	2
1	1.75	1.75
2	1.75	1.75
3	1.5	1.5
4	1.75	1.75
-- 1-bit L2 distance distinguishes sign patterns too
0	7.0711
1	6.7823
2	6.7823
3	6.4807
4	6.7823
-- BFloat16 reconstruction of +-1.0 at precisions 1, 8, 9, 16
2	-2	0.5	-0.5	1.5	-1.5	1	-1
-- Float32 and Float64 reconstruction of +-1.0 at precision 1
2	-2
2	-2
-- Int8 reconstruction of 100 and -100 at precision 1 (cell centre +-64, not 0/-128)
64	-64
-- Zero cell: reduced-precision cosine of identical zero BFloat16 vectors is 0, not 1
0
-- Zero coordinate reconstructs to 0 at precision >= 2 (to +centre at precision 1) for BFloat16, Float32, Float64
2	0	0
2	0	0
2	0	0
-- Int8 keeps the unconditional centre for its all-zero cell
32
-- Exponent-truncation reconstruction stays bounded (no magnitude explosion)
1.4	3.5
-- Signed zero (-0.0) reconstructs to a zero, not a subnormal (mantissa-truncation regime)
0	0	0	0
-- Infinity stays infinite (not NaN) in the mantissa-truncation regime
inf	-inf	inf	inf	-inf
-- Odd (non-multiple-of-8) dimensions: padded lanes never contribute
2	0	0
2	0
64	-64	64
-- NaN policy in the mantissa-truncation regime: NaN with kept payload bit stays NaN, NaN with dropped payload -> inf
nan	inf	nan	inf	nan	inf
-- Float32 precision 16 (downcast boundary): midpoint applied, not the lower edge
1.00390625	1.0078125	1	1.03125
